# Game Component Rules

> Path scope: `src/components/**`, `src/game/store/**`

## Component Architecture

- Each component gets its own file â€” no multi-component files.
- Components are **functional** with hooks â€” no class components.
- Props must have a dedicated `type` or `interface` (e.g., `SuspectCardProps`).
- Default exports are forbidden â€” use named exports only.

## State Management (Zustand)

```typescript
// Single game store â€” do NOT create multiple stores.
// All game state lives in useGameStore.
const useGameStore = create<GameState>()((set, get) => ({
  // state + actions co-located
}));
```

- Components read state via selectors: `const clues = useGameStore(s => s.revealedClues)`.
- **Never** spread the entire store: `const store = useGameStore()` is forbidden.
- Actions live inside the store, not in components.
- Derived state uses selectors or `useMemo`, never stored separately.

## Component Responsibilities

| Component | Owns | Does NOT own |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `SuspectGrid` | Rendering 3Ă—3 grid, tap handlers, guilty/innocent visual state | Puzzle logic, clue text |
| `CluePanel` | Clue display, reveal animation, clue counter | Which clues to show (store decides) |
| `DeductionBoard` | Player mark tracking UI, submission button | Validation logic (store decides) |
| `ShareCard` | Emoji grid generation, clipboard copy | Stats persistence |
| `StatsModal` | Stats display, distribution chart | Stats computation (hook/store) |
| `GameHeader` | Title, timer, menu | Game state |

## Styling

- Use **Tailwind CSS** exclusively â€” no inline `style` objects, no CSS modules, no styled-components.
- Dark noir theme palette (defined in `tailwind.config.ts`):
  - Background: slate-900, slate-800
  - Accent: amber-400, amber-500
  - Text: slate-100, slate-300
  - Danger: red-500
  - Success: emerald-500
- Animations use Tailwind's `transition-*` and `animate-*` utilities.
- For complex animations (card flip, confetti), use CSS `@keyframes` in `index.css`.

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must be focusable (`tabIndex`, semantic elements).
- Suspect cards: `role="button"`, `aria-label` with suspect name and status.
- Clue panel: `aria-live="polite"` for new clue announcements.
- Color is never the sole indicator â€” always pair with icons or text labels.
- Keyboard navigation: arrow keys for grid, Enter/Space for selection.

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: base styles target 320px+ screens.
- Breakpoints: `sm` (640px), `md` (768px), `lg` (1024px).
- The 3Ă—3 grid must remain square and centered on all viewports.
- Touch targets: minimum 44Ă—44px on mobile.

## Event Handling

- Click/tap handlers must be debounced if they trigger state transitions.
- No direct DOM manipulation â€” all UI changes flow through React state.
- Event handlers are defined as stable references (`useCallback`) when passed as props.

## File Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Component | PascalCase | `SuspectGrid.tsx` |
| Hook | camelCase with `use` prefix | `useDaily.ts` |
| Store | camelCase | `gameStore.ts` |
| Utility | camelCase | `shareText.ts` |
| Test | `*.test.tsx` / `*.test.ts` | `SuspectGrid.test.tsx` |

## Testing

- Every component must have at least one render test.
- Test user interactions (click suspect, reveal clue, submit guess) â€” not implementation details.
- Use `@testing-library/react` â€” no Enzyme, no shallow rendering.
- Mock the Zustand store for isolated component tests.
